        content: '"I am competent, capable, and I handle my responsibilities with skill." "I contribute meaningfully to my team and my workplace." "I communicate my ideas clearly and they are valued." "I manage my time effectively and prioritize what matters most." "I am growing professionally every single day." These affirmations address the self-doubt that many professionals experience but rarely discuss. Research by Dr. Tomas Chamorro-Premuzic, a professor of business psychology at University College London, shows that confidence at work is correlated with career advancement, influence, and job satisfaction, and that confidence can be deliberately cultivated through cognitive practices including affirmations.',
